  "id": "stifled_ambition",
  "title": "The Narrowing of Possibilities",
  "description": "You've stopped dreaming about what could be, settling for what is.",
  "content": "When people ask about your goals, your mind goes blank. You used to have dreams, maybe, but they've eroded into vague wishes or disappeared entirely. The future feels like more of the same—not terrible, not great, just... continuing. Others talk about their plans with shining eyes, and you feel a dull envy mixed with exhaustion. Wanting things, reaching for things, hoping for things—it all seems like such effort for such uncertain returns.",
