      "text": "Maybe contentment is underrated",
      "description": "Why reach for more when you have enough?",
      "resultText": "You lean into the lack of ambition, reframing it as wisdom rather than limitation. Wanting less means suffering less disappointment. You cultivate gratitude for what you have, stop comparing yourself to others' achievements. There's a peace in this, though others mistake it for resignation. You tell yourself you're evolved, not stuck. But sometimes, in quiet moments, you wonder if you're just afraid.",
